The paper presents a high-fidelity simulator for the development and testing of crowd-driving algorithms, which involves robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and control systems (cs.SY). The simulator supports a wide range of applications, including perception, vehicle control, planning, and end-to-end learning, which are all relevant to these sub-categories. Therefore, cs.RO is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.SY.
